description:
&lt;p&gt;The Royal Marsden NHS Foundation Trust is the largest comprehensive cancer centre in Europe and a leader in the field of cancer care with a successful record of innovation in nursing care, pioneering new treatments and the development of anti-cancer drugs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Band 7 Lung Cancer Clinical Nurse Specialist to come and join our team and work across both Royal Marsden hospital sites. The post holder will have a joint case load of both NHS and private patients who have been diagnosed with lung cancer, mesothelioma or thymoma.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be enthusiastic, experienced and enjoy patient contact whilst working in a multi-disciplinary environment to support the delivery of a high quality service. The successful candidate will need to possess excellent communication skills, be flexible, reliable and be able to organise their workload.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Part Time working hours will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameJo VickJob titleLead NurseEmail addressjoanna.vick@rmh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
